    <div class="meth-box">
      <b>What the benchmarked $/check figures cover:</b> The commercial rates shown (e.g. $1.5–$4.5/check for Nigeria, $2.5–$6.5/check for Ethiopia) reflect the market price charged by providers such as Sumsub, Smile Identity, Jumio, Onfido, Trulioo, and Shufti Pro for a <b>standard identity verification bundle</b> at 1K–10K checks/month. A single billable "check" at <b>Tier 1 (T1)</b> typically comprises: <b>document capture &amp; OCR</b> (MRZ/data-field extraction from a government-issued ID); <b>passive liveness detection</b> (ISO 30107-3 Level 1/2 — confirming a live face, not a photo or replay); <b>1:1 face match</b> (biometric comparison of live selfie against the document portrait); and a <b>basic sanctions/watchlist screen</b>. Higher-volume contracts reduce the per-check rate by 30–60%. OmniTrust's <b>Tier 2 (T2)</b> rate adds a <b>data anchor query</b> — a real-time API call to a national civil registry or credit bureau to cross-validate name, DOB, and ID number; this is reflected in the T2 premium applied in the Tab 3 volume model. <b>Tier 3 (T3)</b> adds a <b>second data anchor</b> (e.g. telco subscriber records) for markets where no single authoritative registry exists. The OmniTrust rate targets 45–60% below the T1 commercial benchmark through multi-country volume aggregation and, where a gov't rail is available, direct API integration that bypasses commercial intermediaries.<br><br>
      <b>Pricing methodology:</b> Commercial benchmark sourced from Tier 3 provider rate cards (Sumsub, Smile Identity, Jumio, Onfido, Trulioo, Shufti Pro) at 1K–10K checks/month as of Q1 2025, cross-validated against Tier 1 World Bank ID4D costing studies. The World Bank anchor publication [WB-A] is the primary institutional benchmark once its title is confirmed. OmniTrust rate modelled at 45–60% discount to benchmark midpoint. OmniTrust cost is a working number only.<br><br>
      <b>Gov't rail classification:</b> <em>Mature</em> = API-accessible, enrollment &gt;80%; <em>Partial</em> = national ID exists, limited API or sub-80% coverage; <em>Nascent</em> = digital ID program under 3 years old; <em>None</em> = no national digital ID for eKYC purposes.
